:CHECKLIST
Amazon Methods I Have Actually Tried
[x] Writing the press release before any design work starts on a new feature
[x] Defining what success looks like for the customer before defining the product
[ ] Running a structured narrative review instead of slides for a team meeting
[ ] Defining the single most important metric before launching a new project

:POLL
Which Amazon leadership principle do you find most useful in your own work?
Customer obsession above all other considerations
Bias for action over extended deliberation
Dive deep rather than accepting surface-level answers
Invent and simplify as the default operating mode
